RACE.RACE_TEXT: ALBUQUERQUE RACE 5 6 1/2F Dirt CR: 52. Maiden Claiming Purse 13800. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $6,500.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: BLUE COWGIRL set a clear early pace, raced three wide through the turn, opened up and edged clear for the win. COWGIRLLOVER tracked the early pace, loomed four wide through the turn, couldn't sustain the rally, was no match late and finished second best. MIDNIGHT SUSI was reserved early, raced six wide through the turn, finished evenly late and was along for third. GONE KAT raced in mid pack early, angled out seven wide out of the turn and finished belatedly. ROCKETT'S RED CITY followed the early pace, angled towards the inside early stretch and weakened late. MORATTA bumped at the start, was outrun early, raced four wide through the turn and offered no rally. LEONA was allowed to settle early, raced five wide into the turn and gave way. BULLDACIOUS KROME was taken back early, angled in early stretch and never fired. ICY REBEL was unhurried early, raced between rivals out of the turn and flattened out. Race was Hand Timed.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: ALBUQUERQUE RACE 6 5F Dirt CR: 88. Claiming Purse 25800. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON TWO RACES SINCE MARCH 7, 2023 OR WHICH HAVE NOT WON A RACE SINCE JUNE 7, 2023 OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $12,500.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: ROCKY BAR SIX was up close early, went seven wide into the turn, took control in mid stretch, drifted out and was best. CERVEZA was unhurried early, raced six wide through the turn, was gaining late and finished second best. FOLLOW THE FACTS set a pressured early pace, raced three wide into the turn, drifted out through the turn, kept on and weakened late. CANYON DEL ORO was allowed to settle early, raced six wide into the turn and flattened out. A GEM IS A GEM was reserved early from the inside and finished belatedly. PARTYOFSIXTEEN was taken back early, raced eight wide through the turn, passed rivals and finished belatedly. SOLID GOLD BAR pressed the early pace, raced four wide into the turn, angled in and tired. ON A WARPATH forced the early pace, raced five wide into the turn, was squeezed through the turn and faded. SILVERWIND was void of any early sped, saved ground into the turn, angled out through the stretch and offered no rally. FABSTRACTION tracked the early pace, raced six wide and was empty. THE STEWARDS POSTED AN INQUIRY IN REGARDS TO AN INCIDENT IN THE TURN AND TOOK NO ACTION. Race was Hand Timed.

MISS JAX was allowed to settle early, advanced six wide through the turn, was gaining steadily and needed more ground. MISS CONTINENTAL was up close early, raced five wide into the turn and weakened late. UNDO THE RIGHT was reserved early, raced seven wide through the turn, angled in mid stretch and finished with a mild late rally. SAGANAKI raced in mid pack early, went four wide into the turn, angled out in the stretch and offered no le rally. SIMPERING SMILE was outrun early from the inside and never fired. HEMATITE was void of any early speed, raced three wide and was never a threat. DANIEL'S GIRL was taken back early, raced four wide through the turn and was no factor. Race was Hand Timed.
